  "title": "WSHO cum ECO",
  "description": "<p><strong>WSHO cum ECO</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Visit www.ppsjob.com.sg</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain the company’s environmental health standards.</li>\n  <li>Ensure full compliance with safety, housekeeping, erosion control, and mosquito breeding prevention.</li>\n  <li>Achieve zero safety demerit points from MOM, other agencies, and developers.</li>\n  <li>Continuously improve EHS systems by implementing ISO14001 and OHSAS18001 standards.</li>\n  <li>Implement pollution control, material waste management, and 3-R (Reduce, Reuse, Recycle) programmes.</li>\n  <li>Conduct EHS training for workers, staff, and site personnel.</li>\n  <li>Perform site inspections to ensure facilities and equipment are safe and environmentally compliant.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and submit Site Environmental Control Programme and Reports.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Registered Workplace Safety &amp; Health Officer (WSHO) with MOM.</li>\n  <li>Registered Environmental Control Officer (ECO) with NEA.</li>\n  <li>Completed Risk Management Training Course.</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of relevant experience.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Apply now to help maintain a safe and healthy environment!</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Visit www.ppsjob.com.sg</strong></p>",
